Infographic: Assembly elections 2017: Decoding pockets of influence 
12-3-2017 
Assembly elections 2017: Decoding pockets of influence

Official poll data doesn’t allow us to track the voting behaviour of communities or castes. But analysing results in reserved seats or in ones where specific communities — like Muslims — are known to have a larger presence than elsewhere helps decode the verdict, though the pattern need not necessarily reflect the voting of that community. 
